<div id="review_2092146975" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2092146975" />
    <a title="Sairam Krishnan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8056568-sairam-krishnan"><img alt="Sairam Krishnan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1478231226p2/8056568.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2092146975?book_show_action=true">Aug 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sairam Krishnan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sairam Krishnan" href="/user/show/8056568-sairam-krishnan">Sairam Krishnan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780571218769" href="/book/show/7017366-english-august">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2092146975" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16399593303711555338">What a story! Upamanyu&apos;s Chatterjee&apos;s 1988 novel is an absolute delight, and so is Agastya Sen&apos;s terrible aimlessness. Seldom have I been made to laugh and think so much, and almost never have I read something this seeped in self-mockery. English, August is nothing short of a modern classic, and I will definitely come back to it again and again for the sheer dark enjoyment it brought me.</span>
  <span id="freeText16399593303711555338" style="display:none">What a story! Upamanyu's Chatterjee's 1988 novel is an absolute delight, and so is Agastya Sen's terrible aimlessness. Seldom have I been made to laugh and think so much, and almost never have I read something this seeped in self-mockery. English, August is nothing short of a modern classic, and I will definitely come back to it again and again for the sheer dark enjoyment it brought me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16399593303711555338" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


